cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task, hence it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The paper also proposes a novel Loss Weight Module that aims to improve the robustness of the model, which involves optimizing the loss function, indicating that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. Additionally, the paper leverages depth information to improve semantic segmentation, which could fall under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The proposed method also involves multi-scale side outputs, which could be related to the cs.RO (Robotics) category. Finally, the paper evaluates its method on benchmark datasets, which could be related to the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
